<TITLE>PACIFIC EXCHANGE HALTS TRADING ON SOME OPTIONS</TITLE>
<DATELINE>    SAN FRANCISCO, Oct 20 - </DATELINE><BODY>The Pacific Stock Exchange said it
has halted trading in the options of 30 stocks because of the
conditions in the market in the underlying securities.
    The exchange normally handles trading in the options of
about 117 stocks, a spokeswoman said.
